loads/2025/04/sticky-apricot-pork-tenderloin-4-728x485.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/sticky-apricot-pork-tenderloin-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/sticky-apricot-pork-tenderloin-4-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/sticky-apricot-pork-tenderloin-4-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/sticky-apricot-pork-tenderloin-4-150x100.jpg 150w\" data-lazy-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/sticky-apricot-pork-tenderloin-4-scaled.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eThen, I pour the mixture into the pan with the pork. It helps to deglaze the pan and also simmers and thickens a bit more. I spoon it over the pork too. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eTime for the oven! The whole pan goes right into the oven for about 20 minutes or so. You will be surprised at how quickly it cooks! Just make sure to take the internal temp. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003e\u003cspan\u003eTHAT’S IT. How easy is that? \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/sticky-apricot-pork-tenderloin-7-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"sticky apricot pork tenderloin\" width=\"1651\" height=\"2200\" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt=\"\" data-jpibfi-post-url=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2025/04/sticky-apricot-pork-tenderloin/\" data-jpibfi-post-title=\"Sticky Apricot Pork Tenderloin.\" data-jpibfi-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/sticky-apricot-pork-tenderloin-7-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/sticky-apricot-pork-tenderloin-7-scaled.jpg 1651w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/sticky-apricot-pork-tenderloin-7-728x970.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/sticky-aprico